<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Public Works/40: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-20T18:00:00-05:00">March 20, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>24. Your 28, March 14, 5 p.m. Minister Skinner has just telegraphed from
                                Athens<note n="14" xml:id="d75fn14">Telegram not printed.</note>
                            that the Greek Minister in Italy on February 18 informed his Government
                            that the instructions of the Italian Government to its delegate on the
                            International Financial Commission were in a sense favorable to the
                            Commission’s accepting the service of the Seligman loan. Please consult
                            your Greek colleague and inform the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>